<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-770-549  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 770 549.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Journal of the Association for Computing Machinery  Oct 1990 v37n4 p712(8).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>A correction of the termination conditions of the Henschen-Naqvitechnique. (technical)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Briggs, David A.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The technique described by Henschen and Naqvi translates querieson recursively defined relations of a Datalog data base intoiterative programs that invoke a query processor.andP;  The basis ofthe technique is associating with a recursively defined relationan infinite set of nonrecursive rules when the collective resultsdecide the extension of the recursively defined relation.andO;Recasting the Henschen and Naqvi algorithm as a graph traversalshows an error in the termination conditions.andP;  Using a graphicalrepresentation of the computation based on a formal representationof rule expansions corrects the termination condition.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     AlgorithmsData BasesQuery Languages.andO;Feature:   illustrationchart.andO;Caption:   Relevant parts of the example. (chart)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>